    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A class of elastomers  that is notable for performance at low temperatures, resilience, and abrasion resistance. Used for shoe heels and soles, gaskets, and belting. Combined with other rubbers to improve their resilience and flexibility at low temperatures.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000048651/Brady, et al, Materials Handbook (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093795/Encyclopedia Britannica Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>以耐低溫、堅韌耐磨等特性著稱的一種彈性體，可製成鞋跟、鞋底、密封墊圈、傳動皮帶。若與其他種橡膠混合，可強化其於低溫下的韌性和彈性。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
